RUSSEL MOLEFE African Times News Digital Edition | www.africantimesnews.co.za | @AfricanTimesSA TWO people died and four others, including two police officers sustained serious injuries in a head-on collision along the N1 south outside Polokwane, Limpopo, today, Thursday 12 April 2018. The accident happened at about 8am, according to police spokesperson Lt.Col Moatshe Ngoepe. Ngoepe said a police vehicle with two officers was travelling from the southern direction when it collided head-on with a VW Polo with four occupants. “Two occupants from the VW died on the scene whilst the other occupants and the two police officers sustained serious injuries, and they were all taken to the hospital for medical treatment. The police are investigating a case of culpable homicide,” Ngoepe said.